content: Diving into AI-assisted coding tools. Cursor AI is surprisingly intuitive. Could speed up my side project significantly.
Spent the last few days reflecting on my leave of absence. Realizing it wasn't a setback, but a detour that enriched my perspective.
Just turned 22, and I'm using this milestone to pivot my career. Aiming for a role in green tech or blockchain governance. Big dreams, bigger city.
Outlined a project proposal integrating AI into urban energy management. It's ambitious, but if it works, it could be a game-changer.
Attended a tech meetup in Brooklyn. Met someone working on blockchain solutions for supply chains. We're planning a coffee meet-up to discuss potential collaborations.
Setbacks on my side project. The AI model isn't integrating smoothly with urban planning data. Time to troubleshoot and maybe pivot.
Reached out to an old classmate from NYU now working at a green tech firm. Hoping for some insider info or a referral.
Had that coffee meet-up. They're interested in my project but want to see a working prototype. Back to the drawing board with more energy.
Celebrated small wins. Got the AI model to finally sync with urban planning data. It’s not perfect, but it's a start.
Applied for a position at a firm specializing in AI for sustainability. Used my travel insights to highlight my unique perspective.
Mentor session today. We talked about the implications of AI in governance. I'm thinking about how this could shape my project.
The prototype is coming along, but the complexity of urban energy systems is making me question if AI can truly solve this.
Networking pays off. Got an interview with the tech firm for next week. They're intrigued by my project idea.
As I turn 22, I'm realizing that every setback is just a setup for a comeback. Excited to see where this journey takes me next.
